        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 11:45PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1144 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Follett, or 11 miles north of Lipscomb, moving
south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lipscomb, Booker, Follett, Higgins, Darrouzett, Elmwood, Slapout,
Glazier, and Balko.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
